    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Belize should include evacuation provisions:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> $5,000+ deductible; pay cash locally for routine care</li>
    <li><strong>Mexico focus:</strong> Chetumal, Mexico (90 min away) has better hospitals; some use Mexico-focused coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Supplemental evacuation:</strong> SkyMed or Medjet ($300-500/year) adds dedicated evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>Local cash:</strong> Routine Belize care is cheap; save insurance for major issues</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American QRP Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month Social Security. Moving to San Ignacio.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> GeoBlue international plan with US coverage. Add Medjet evacuation membership.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$400/month GeoBlue + $25/month Medjet. Full US hospital access if evacuated.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Retiring to Ambergris Caye. £3,000/month combined pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with comprehensive evacuation. Covers UK visits and US evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$1,000/month combined. Essential given limited island healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Canadian Snowbird, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> 6 months Belize (winter), 6 months Canada. Maintains Canadian coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for worldwide. Canada covered when there; evacuation from Belize if needed.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$380/month. Canadian healthcare plus international for Belize.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How bad is Belize healthcare really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For routine care—infections, minor injuries, basic tests—it's adequate and affordable. For anything serious—heart attack, cancer, complex surgery—you'll be evacuated. The main hospital lacks many specialists and advanced equipment. Plan insurance accordingly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Where would I be evacuated to?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Usually Houston, Miami, or Mexico City depending on condition and insurance. Chetumal, Mexico (90 min by car) handles many non-emergency needs. Guatemala City is another option. Air ambulance to US is typical for serious emergencies.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What does the QRP program include?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        QRP grants permanent residency, tax exemption on foreign income, duty-free import of household goods and vehicle (once), and the right to live and work (own business) in Belize. The $2,000/month requirement must come from approved sources like pension or Social Security.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Belize safe for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Outside Belize City's rougher areas, Belize is generally safe. Tourist areas and expat communities have low crime. Exercise normal precautions. The QRP community is established and supportive. Hurricane season (June-November) requires preparation, especially on cayes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with strong evacuation coverage for Belize.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/geoblue" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get GeoBlue Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Belize authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
